title: Frieze, 1905–15
description: Mission style. Border printed two across (mirror). Alternating rectangular shapes with stylized floral and geometric patterns (key patterns and other geometric designs). The flowers in the smaller rectangles are a set of three tulips and in the larger rectangles are flowering bushes set above two large flowers. The bottom has a scalop design with floral bushes.All forms are outlined in beading. Ungrounded and covered in a grid. Printed in pink liquid mica, green and brown.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-486.
